name: Reminiscence
description:
Zine // Photo Story

When I try to recall my childhood memories, I feel lost. 
That memories are like fragments of other people’s thoughts that implanted in my mind. There are a few memories left that I can remember, and the rest is vague.

One day, I started photographing my daughter’s belongings and several items in our home, with the aim of recollecting my childhood memories, which fade with age.
